                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.63/454</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Fletcher</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-20T17:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 20, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>113. By circular just published all transactions relative to mining properties
                    made with mining agencies of the State of Oaxaca from June 3, 1915, to March 3,
                    1916; are declared null and void because the State of Oaxaca refused obedience
                    to the Carranza Government during that time and interested parties are given
                    until June 15 next to renew these transactions with the Department Commerce and
                    Industry.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
